Executive Technical Summary

This document presents the conceptual engineering architecture of the PI220 VHX-220 propulsion platform and the AERP-220 (Adaptive Energy Recovery Platform), a modular electro-hydraulic subsystem intended for future research into adaptive energy management, predictive vehicle control, modular serviceability, and integrated chassis support.

The reviewed architecture combines distributed electric propulsion, electro-hydraulic actuation, predictive control algorithms, modular subsystem integration, and intelligent supervisory control through the PI220 CORE architecture.

The objective is to investigate advanced mobility concepts through a modular engineering platform suitable for future simulation, prototype development, and experimental validation.

